Requirements
‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾

  In order to use the small 8-color-backdrops you need:

  * An AMIGA ;-) with at least Kick 2.0+ (3.0 recommended)

  * A properly installed MagicWB of Martin Huttenloher
    or under WB 2.0/2.1 NickPrefs (AmiNET util/wb/NickPrefs.lha)

  To use the BIG 16-color-pictures you need

  * A PNG-datatype, e.g. from AmiNET (util/dtype/png_dt.lha),
    because the pictures are in this format

  * A program to setup the 16 colors on WB, e.g. MagicWB-Demon
    or LockColors from AmiNET 'util/cdity/lockcolors1_1a.lha'

  * Internet access - so you can send me e-mail with @{"comments" LINK "Author"}!

@ENDNODE


@NODE "Installation" "Installation..."
@NEXT "Author"
@PREV "Requirements"
@TOC "MAIN"

Installation
‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾‾

  First install a PNG-datatype (see @{"requirements" LINK "Requirements"}).

  Then you have to setup the right colors - therfore you will
  need a programs which locks them (see @{"requirements" LINK "Requirements"}).
  Set your colors to

  Color  R   G   B
  -----------------
   0   149 149 149 --+
   1     0   0   0   |
   2   255 255 255   |
   3    59 103 162   +-- MagicWB colors
   4   123 123 123   |
   5   175 175 175   |
   6   170 144 124   |
   7   255 169 151 --+
   8     0   0 255 --+
   9    40  62  91   |
  10    96 128  96   |
  11   226 209 119   +-- Extended Rom-Colors
  12   255 212 203   |
  13   122  96  72   |
  14   210 210 210   |
  15   229  93  93 --+

  For example start you MagicWB-Demon like this:
  Run <>NIL: MagicWB-Demon 4,123,123,123 5,175,175,175 6,170,144,124 7,255,169,151 8,0,0,255 9,40,62,91  10,96,128,96 11,226,209,119 12,255,212,203 13,122,96,72 14,210,210,210 15,229,93,93

  Then drop the pictures into your 'pattern-directory' and
  choose a background with the 'WBPattern' program!

  Have fun!

@ENDNODE


